<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is a good AI citability score?</strong></p>
<p>A score above 70 out of 100 indicates strong citability. Most content that gets cited by AI platforms scores in the 75 to 95 range. Below 50 signals structural or technical issues that prevent AI systems from parsing and referencing your content effectively.</p>
<p><strong>Does AI citability score affect Google rankings?</strong></p>
<p>Not directly. AI citability score is a separate metric from Google's ranking algorithm. However, many of the same factors (structured data, E-E-A-T, content freshness) influence both. Improving your citability score typically improves your traditional SEO performance as well.</p>
<p><strong>How do I check if AI is citing my content?</strong></p>
<p>Search for your brand name or specific content phrases in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews. Tools like Averi AI and OptimizeCamp track citations automatically. You can also monitor referral traffic from AI platforms in <a href="/blog/google-analytics-4-setup/">Google Analytics</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Do nofollow links affect AI citability?</strong></p>
<p>No. AI citability is not based on link equity. It depends on content structure, factual density, authority signals, and crawler access. A page with zero backlinks but excellent structure and schema markup can score higher than a page with hundreds of backlinks but poor formatting.</p>
<p><strong>Is AI citability the same as GEO?</strong></p>
<p>AI citability score is one metric within the broader <a href="/blog/what-is-geo/">GEO (Generative Engine Optimization)</a> discipline. GEO covers all strategies for optimizing content for AI search platforms. The citability score specifically measures how likely a given page is to be cited. GEO includes citability plus content strategy, platform analysis, and technical optimization.</p>
<p><strong>Can Stacc help improve my AI citability score?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Every article Stacc publishes follows AI citability best practices: structured headings, schema markup, answer-first formatting, internal and external citations, and regular freshness updates. Our 92% average SEO score reflects optimization for both traditional search and AI citation.</p>
